      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "The FEA software (Ansys Mechanical) is used under a validated installation with documented version control, regression testing, and change management procedures consistent with FDA software quality guidance. SQA records were reviewed and found compliant."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 and Ansys verification manual were executed. Results matched analytic solutions within 0.5% for linear elastic beam and contact benchmark cases relevant to this construct geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh convergence study was performed across three refinement levels. The Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) for construct stiffness was less than 1.2%, satisfying the required discretization error threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Direct sparse solver residuals were monitored for all load steps. Force and moment equilibrium residuals remained below 1e-6 relative tolerance. No convergence failures were observed across the full ensemble of 11 construct configurations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Model setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing were performed by two independent analysts following a documented simulation protocol. Results were cross-checked and discrepancies resolved prior to final submission. Independent review confirmed no systematic use errors."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum mechanics with frictional contact at the screw-rod interface was selected as the model form. Justification for linearity is supported by the small-displacement regime of ASTM F1717 compression-bending testing. Sensitivity analyses confirmed that nonlinear geometry effects are negligible below the 2% offset yield criterion."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus, Poisson ratio) were obtained from ASTM F136 coupon testing performed on the same lot material as the test constructs. Geometric dimensions were measured via CMM with traceable calibration. Input uncertainty was propagated using a one-at-a-time sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories. Sample provenance, lot traceability, and dimensional inspection records were documented. The sample population is representative of the production geometry used in the FEA model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single load condition (compression-bending at 5 degrees) per the ASTM F1717 protocol. Only one test condition was evaluated, which limits the breadth of validation coverage. This factor is below the required level; the gap is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation activity scope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "A formal mapping between experimental setup parameters and FEA boundary conditions was documented. Fixture geometry, loading point locations, and constraint conditions in the simulation were verified to match the physical test configuration through dimensional inspection records and photographic documentation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness (N/mm) was the primary quantity of interest. FEA predictions fell within the 95% confidence interval of the experimental distribution for 10 of 11 constructs. Mean prediction error was 4.1% across the ensemble. Statistical comparison used a two-sided t-test at alpha=0.05."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness under compression-bending is the regulatory quantity of interest for Class II spinal fixation device submissions per FDA guidance. The QoI directly informs the device mechanical performance claim and is the output predicted by the FEA model ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the ASTM F1717 test configuration used to characterize the device. The experimental constructs are geometrically and materially identical to those modeled. The validation scenario is therefore highly relevant to the intended simulation use, supporting confidence in model predictions for the compression-bending performance claim."
    }
  ],
